Red lentil & squash dhal
Method
Put the oil and the onion in a saucepan, and cook for 5 mins.
Stir in the garlic and cook for a further 1 min, then stir in the spices
and butternut squash. Combine everything together.
Tip in the chopped tomatoes, stock and chutney, and season
well. Bring to the boil, then gently simmer for about 10 mins. Add
the lentils and simmer for another 20 mins until the lentils and
squash are tender. Stir in the coriander and serve with warmed
naan bread.
